gomodel:SYNGO_2550  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6: \"Ultrastructural organization of Ng in dendritic spines\"\n- \"Interestingly, Ng localization at the extrasynaptic membrane (within the spine) reveals a non-uniform distribution, in which there is a minimal concentration midway between the PSD edge and the furthest tangential point (Supplementary Figure 6C), an area within the spine that is well characterized as the endocytic zone (Blanpied et al, 2002; Racz et al, 2004; Lu et al, 2007).\"\n\nSince localization to endocytic zone is suggested but not shown, I have not used this term.. Experimental description: - Species of tissues used is not stated in the paper. It is derived from the species of the used shRNA constructs: \"Five different unique 19-nucleotide sequences targeting rat Ng were designed and pSuper RNAi system, ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-16" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2550" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

